 billion, with the share value decreasing to IDR 50 from IDR 100. The announcement was positively received by the market, with the share price increasing by IDR 20 to IDR 780 at the closing bell, representing a 6.12% increase over the past week.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51684/planning-stock-split-samf-idr-climb", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies"], "tags": ["Stock Splits", "IDX", "IDX Composite", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-12-09T13:58:08", "title": "PT Saraswati Anugerah Makmur to Conduct 1:2 Stock Split on February 5, 2025, Following Shareholder Approval"}, {"body": "The Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX) has modified its regulation to allow more stocks to be tradable during pre-opening and pre-closing periods, resulting in a more extensive price discovery process and a better reflection of general market conditions. The Jakarta Composite Index responded positively, rising 0.36% or 26.80 points to 7,409.59, with a transaction volume of 203.15 million shares valued at IDR 38.71 trillion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51683/allowing-pre-opening-stocks-ihsg-increase-morning", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies"], "tags": ["IDX", "IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-12-09T13:26:11", "title": "Indonesia Stock Exchange Expands Tradable Stocks During Pre-Opening and Pre-Closing Periods"}, {"body": "PT Tempo Inti Media Tbk (TMPo) shares surged 34.43% to close at Rp164, with foreign investors recording a net buy of 113,000 shares, amid a total outstanding share count of 1.05 billion. The company's free float stood at 25.02%, with controlling shareholders holding 74.51% and non-controlling shareholders holding 25.49% of the shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51677/tmpo-reigns-gainers-week-closing", "sub_sector": ["media-entertainment"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Foreign Investor", "IDX Composite", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["TMPO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-06T18:24:39", "title": "PT Tempo Inti Media TBK shares surge 34.43% to close at Rp164 on Friday."}, {"body": "The Jakarta Stock Price Composite Index fell 0.18% or 13.45 points to 7,313.31 due to massive downturns in state-owned issuers, led by PT Bank Mandiri Tbk (BMRI) with a 3.53% decline, PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI) with a 2.07% slip, PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk (TLKM) with a 2.64% contraction, and PT Bank Negara Indonesia Tbk (BBNI) with a 2.63% slippage. The index's correction was a reversal of its positive trend over the past two days, with a total transaction volume of 14.90 billion shares valued at IDR 9.44 trillion and a transaction frequency of 1.19 million across all markets.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51666/soes-lagged-ihsg-decrease", "sub_sector": ["banks", "banks", "telecommunication", "banks"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["BMRI.JK", "BBRI.JK", "TLKM.JK", "BBNI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-06T06:07:28", "title": "Jakarta Stock Price Composite Index Falls 0.18% Due to Downturns in State-Owned Issuers"}, {"body": "Indonesia Stock Exchange authorities will improve stock investment literacy to increase awareness and prudence among retail investors, recognizing the importance of educating potential investors about the risks involved in capital market investments. This move comes after President Prabowo Subianto compared stock investment to gambling, highlighting the risks faced by small investors who may inevitably lose out to bigger players.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 1, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51656/preventing-gambling-mindset-idx-continue-educate-investors", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Sentiment", "Bearish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-12-05T11:43:22", "title": "Indonesian Stock Exchange Authorities to Boost Financial Literacy Among Retail Investors"}]